    <h3 class="poetry-title">III. GLITCH DHARMA</h3>
    <div class="poem-text">
      <p>Confusion is sacred.<br>We are <a href="https://aeon.co/essays/the-hard-problem-of-consciousness-is-a-distraction-from-the-real-one" target="_blank" class="subtle-link" data-tooltip="Anil Seth: We are controlled hallucinations">hallucinations</a> who hallucinate ourselves.<br>Recursive loops crowning new revelations<br>until the whole circus dissolves.</p>
      <p>In the splintered mirrors, see:<br>There has never been purity,<br>only fecund wreckage,<br>only love risking language<br>in an endless void</p>
      
